1. Cnidi: a center of the wor- ship of Aphrodite in Caria. In her shrine there was a statue of the goddess by Praxiteles, of which the Vatican Venus is a copy.— Paphi: Aphrodite's ancient home in Cyprus, where tradition said the goddess was born from the foam of the sea.
